## Use Case: Remediation Workflow

### Apply NetworkPolicies via Kimera

```bash
# 1. Verify Cilium enforcement is active
uv run kimera enforce enable

# 2. Apply restrictive NetworkPolicies (LLM-generated or config-driven)
uv run kimera -n unguard generate-policies --dry-run   # review first
uv run kimera -n unguard generate-policies --apply     # apply after review

# Alternative: use Kimera's secure command (config-driven, no LLM required)
uv run kimera -n unguard secure missing-network-policies
```

### Verify Remediation

```bash
# Kimera verification
uv run kimera -n unguard verify

# Check policies were created
kubectl get networkpolicies -n unguard

# Re-run exploit demo to confirm ports are CLOSED
uv run kimera -n unguard exploit missing-network-policies --mode demo
```

### Revert (when done testing)

```bash
uv run kimera -n unguard revert missing-network-policies
# Note: Cilium is a cluster-level CNI — do NOT uninstall it when reverting.
# Without NetworkPolicies, all traffic flows freely regardless.
```

