## Smartscape Naming Reference (Unguard)

| Kubernetes Service | Language | Smartscape source_name |
|--------------------|----------|----------------------|
| unguard-like-service | PHP 8.0 / Laravel | `PHP-CLI` or `PHP on unguard-like-service-*` |
| unguard-user-auth-service | Node.js 18 | `bin/www (user-auth-service)` |
| unguard-membership-service | .NET 7 | `MembershipService.dll` |
| unguard-microblog-service | Java 11 Spring | `MicroblogController` |
| unguard-ad-service | .NET 5 | Unknown assembly (no DB connections) |
| unguard-mariadb | MariaDB | `data` |
| unguard-redis | Redis | `Redis` |

**Critical**: `source_name` is the process display name, not the K8s name. Use `target_name`
(K8s pod names) for filtering by service. Use `source_name` only when you know the exact
process display name from a prior Smartscape query.

