## Demo: Unauthorized Lateral Movement (PHP curl from like-service)

This demonstrates a Smartscape-visible attack — unlike `nc` probes, PHP curl IS instrumented
by OneAgent and creates real Smartscape edges.

```bash
# Get like-service pod
LIKE_POD=$(kubectl get pod -n unguard \
  -l app.kubernetes.io/name=like-service \
  -o jsonpath='{.items[0].metadata.name}')

# Run unauthorized HTTP call via PHP curl (OneAgent captures this)
kubectl exec -n unguard "$LIKE_POD" -- php -r "
\$ch = curl_init('http://unguard-user-auth-service/');
curl_setopt(\$ch, CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER, true);
curl_setopt(\$ch, CURLOPT_TIMEOUT, 5);
curl_exec(\$ch);
echo 'HTTP: ' . curl_getinfo(\$ch, CURLINFO_HTTP_CODE) . PHP_EOL;
curl_close(\$ch);
"

# Wait 3-5 minutes, then verify edge appears in Smartscape (Step 5 query above)
```

After applying NetworkPolicies that restrict like-service egress, re-run the same query —
the `PHP-CLI → user-auth-service` edge will be absent.
